13/Dec/2016 04:10 PM;AByrne1;Ashok,

This issue was found in the Bankinter project.

We identified that a refactoring of the class to support Swift Message Highlighting introduced a dependency on the Number 2 line when calculating the context marker positions.

There is no dependency referenced in the Swift Standards.

A code change was made for Bankinter which removed the dependency instead checking for a Number 2 line and where not present then checking for a Number 3.

I discussed this with Edward and the fix needs to go back into the product.

The fix is in the transform() method

{code}
            if (address.length()>0)
            {
                Utils.addValue2Map(map, "50_addr", address, false, true);
                startPosition = value.indexOf("2/");
                //EBE000191-291
                if ( startPosition == -1 ) //Number 2 not present, check for Number 3
                	startPosition = value.indexOf("3/");
                String subTag = value.substring(startPosition);
                //String subTag = value.substring(value.indexOf("2/"));
                List<String> tokens = Arrays.asList(address.split("\\s+"));
                String lastString = tokens.get(tokens.size() - 1);
                String addressTag = subTag.substring(0, subTag.indexOf(lastString) + lastString.length());
                offset = addressTag.length();
                customValuePositionsMap.put("50_addr", new int[]{startPosition, offset});
            }

{code}

