09/Oct/2019 03:51 PM;VSavkoor;Hi Paul,
The issue here is the inability to resume a failed CDD rescore without a server restart. This is because the IDs of Batch_Event go out of sync. The IDs created through Hibernate class cache a default of 10 IDs but those created in the batch process monitor get the next max id. The acquisition cluster plugin which propagates events found in the database ignores the events with IDs that are lower than the one it last processed (lastEventId), and so rescore events get ignored.

We fixed this issue in the ZIONS project by updating the BatchEvent.java hibernate class to pass in the increment_by parameter value of 1 to IdentifierGenerator. For example:
{noformat}
@Id
@GeneratedValue(generator="norkom_generator")
@GenericGenerator(name="norkom_generator", strategy = "com.norkom.base.business.dao.IdentifierGenerator",
    		parameters = {@Parameter(name="table_name", value = "ACQ_BATCH_EVENT"), @Parameter(name="increment_by", value = "1")}
{noformat}

