column74:
OOME (OutOfMemoryException) occurs during memory-profiling, due to a finishLock method not being called.

During normal SM processing, objects are locked, updated and released - ResourceAccess.startLock is used to start a lock and ResourceAccess.finishLock is used to finish the lock.

However, in ProfileStoreMemory.insert(String position, String tablename, Object key, Object value), finishLock is not being called. The one-line fix is to

*REPLACE*
{code}
                	this.resacc.release(trx, this.getAccessResource(key));
{code}

*WITH*
{code}
                	this.resacc.finishLock(trx);
{code}

*in the ProfileStoreMemory method*
{code}
    public void insert(String position, String tablename, Object key, Object value) throws BLAKEException
{code}

After the replacement, the change is

{code}	
    public void insert(String position, String tablename, Object key, Object value) throws BLAKEException
    {
		...
                // INSERT the Profile only when it's not there yet.
                String pkey = makeKey(position, key);
                ResourceLock trx = this.resacc.startLock();
                try {
					...
                }finally {
                	this.resacc.finishLock(trx);
                }
            }
            else 
            	throw new LearnerException("Cannot find table '"+tablename+"'");
{code}

Note that, most of our customer use DB-profiling and very few use memory-profiling. BT (BrtishTelecom) is an example of a customer who do use memory-profiling.

Nonetheless, this fix needs to be incorporated into Platform, in case more customers choose to use memory-profiling, in the future.

