In Nordea project (6.1.2.124 / 3.2) we call WLM functionality using webservice. NOTE: this was Nordea's requirement NOT to have *[CDATA[....]]* xml elements so we receive and send SOAP requests/responses in fully structured XML format.

As a parto of the whole configuration in the Services Manager the  *<wlmResult>* generated by EXTENDED-WLM-PROCESS function - is processed as XML document using XQUERY in database. All goes ok until there is special character like *&* for example:
{code}<matchData>
                  <matchDataItem>
                     <input>
                        <cm>Fifteenth Ocean GmbH  Co. KG</cm>
                     </input>
                     <fieldValue>Fifteenth Ocean GmbH & Co. KG</fieldValue>
                  </matchDataItem>
               </matchData>{code}

Ampersand makes further processing impossible because of non well-formed XML.

The investigation done by Per Solberg shows that {code}com.norkom.wlm.business.realtime.impl.ExtendedWLMRealTimeFunction{code} class is NOT generating well-formed XML:

{code}    private void dataToXml(Object data, StringBuffer buff, String parent)
    {
        if (data instanceof Map)
        {
            Iterator iter = ((Map) data).keySet().iterator();
            while (iter.hasNext())
            {
                String key = (String) iter.next();
                Object value = ((Map) data).get(key);
                buff.append("<").append(key).append(">");
                dataToXml(value, buff, key);
                buff.append("</").append(key).append(">");
            }
        }
        else if (data instanceof List)
        {
            String tag = parent.endsWith("es") ? parent.substring(0, parent.length() - 2)
                    : parent.endsWith("s") ? parent.substring(0, parent.length() - 1) : parent + "Item";
            for (int i = 0; i < ((List) data).size(); i++)
            {
                buff.append("<").append(tag).append(">");
                dataToXml(((List) data).get(i), buff, tag);
                buff.append("</").append(tag).append(">");
            }
        }
        else
        {
            buff.append(data);
        }
    }
{code}

We need this to be fixed

