column74:
The problem is in the DataSourceField class.
It has a collection of DataSourceFieldInputData objects.
The mapping key is defined as DataSourceFieldInputData.EXT_DS_FIELD_ID
However, when Hibernate constructs the query, it uses the DataSourceFieldInputData.DS_FIELD_ID column to link the entries.
This causes a mismapping in entries, ultimately causing the transliteration (extended) field never being populated with data.
The original Hibernate Annotation uses:
{code}
 @OneToMany(mappedBy="dataSourceField")
    @LazyCollection(LazyCollectionOption.FALSE)
    @Cascade(value = CascadeType.DELETE)
    @OrderBy(clause="ORD_NO asc")
    @org.hibernate.annotations.BatchSize(size=50)
    public Set<DataSourceFieldInputData> getInputDataSourceFields()
    {
        return this.inputDataSourceFields;
    }
{code}

This is how it is defined by default and works for other mappings.
However, for this particular situation it didn't work because it caused the issue.
I changed the DataSourceField annotations to 
{code}
 @OneToMany(targetEntity=DataSourceFieldInputData.class)
    @JoinColumn(name="EXT_DS_FIELD_ID",referencedColumnName="ID")
    @LazyCollection(LazyCollectionOption.FALSE)
    @Cascade(value = CascadeType.DELETE)
    @org.hibernate.annotations.BatchSize(size=50)
    public Set<DataSourceFieldInputData> getInputDataSourceFields()
    {
        return this.inputDataSourceFields;
    }
{code}

I also changed the DataSourceFieldInputData annotations from :
{code}
 @ManyToOne
    @JoinColumn(name="EXT_DS_FIELD_ID", nullable=false, unique=false)
    public DataSourceField getExtendedDataSourceField()
    {
        return extendedDataSourceField;
    }
{code}

To :
{code}
@ManyToOne
    @JoinColumn(name="EXT_DS_FIELD_ID", referencedColumnName="ID",nullable=false, unique=false)
    public DataSourceField getExtendedDataSourceField()
    {
        return extendedDataSourceField;
    }
{code}
This actually worked and fixed the issue. 
So far no side effects noticed.
I was just trying an alternative form of defining the collection, and I'm not really sure why this worked and the default did not.

