{color:#000000}Permissions for the management of both internal wlm standard list  and external lists (worldcheck , fpfa , dowjones ) in Out of the Box NetReveal product does not meet business requirements. {color}

{color:#000000}Essentially, these permissions have not been designed in a way where permissions are 'read only' or 'editable' nor are the permissions nimble enough such that permissions can be easily modified to meet the requirements. Therefore, users that wish to have 'view only' access should not be in a position to have access to modify rule filters and list entries.{color}

{color:#000000} {color}

{color:#000000}The change seeks the ability for additional security permissions to be provided so that buttons to access the filters (eg. edit, delete), indexes (eg. build indexes, edit, delete), lists & list management (keywords) can be isolated from user roles such that it cannot be accessed, creation of a 'view only' capability will be available to configure.  {color}

{color:#000000} {color}

{color:#000000}Currently in APAC region, there are multiple clients that are asking for true read only wlm standard list and watch list user screens. Current Product behaviour does not give that desired functionality.{color}

{color:#000000}User is still able to edit/delete list filters, rebuild/create/delete indexes.{color}

{color:#000000} {color}

{color:#000000}If we turn off the parameter filtering.editable.list=false, system will make it complete read only, where users will not be able to export list data.{color}

{color:#000000}Ideally we need to add permissions on the in question system filter / index sections and user should be able to configure them through base configuration changes to get the read only flavour. {color}

{color:#000000} {color}

{color:#000000}Could you please provide your view on this? Do you think this functionality needs to be enhanced in the product?{color}

